Nigeria’s Vice President, Prof. Yemi Osinbajo is scheduled to pay one day official visit to Abia State, on Monday. While details of Osinbajo’s visit to the state is still sketchy, our reporter gathered that part of the places that he will be visiting is the National War Museum located at Ebite, Amafor Isingwu in Umuahia North LGA. Information gathered by our reporter has it that repairs were going on within and outside the facility including painting work. The Chief of Staff to the Governor, Dr. Anthony Agbazuere in the company of other government officials on Sunday visited to inspect the ongoing renovation work at the museum. A press release by the Chief Press Secretary to the governor, Mr. Onyebuchi Ememanka read “The Governor of Abia State, Okezie Ikpeazu, Phd “On behalf of the Government and People of Abia State, “Joyfully welcomes His Excellency, Professor Yemi Osinbajo, GCON, SAN “Vice President of the Federal Republic of Nigeria “To Abia State on a One Day Working Visit. “Date – Monday, January 27th, 2020. “Our dear Vice President, “Welcome yet again to Abia, God’s Own State. “Please be assured of the usual warm hospitality of our people.”